public class AttachmentsVOImpl
extends OAViewObjectImpl

The implementation of the View Object for Attachments. All additions/deletions/retrievals of attachment records should be done via this View Object. AttachmentsVO is comprised of three Entity Objects FndAttachedDocumentsEO, FndDocumentEntitiesEO and FndDocumentEntitiesEO. Both FndDocumentEntitiesEO and FndDocumentEntitiesEO are both reference Entities however FndDocumentEntitiesEO is also updatable. The methods in this VOImpl have been designed specifically to manage the FndDocumentEntitiesEO instance used as part of this VO which will not happen automatically in the framework since it is a reference entity. Any view links that are linked to AttachmentsVO should always map to EntityName and should have at least one mapping to one of the five Pk Value columns (Pk1Value-Pk5Value). Any View Object which links to AttachmentsVO must have the EntityName and the relevant Pk Values set before the view link is dereferenced.

setAccessorValues

public void setAccessorValues(oracle.jbo.ViewObject masterVO,
                              oracle.jbo.server.ViewLinkDefImpl vlDef)
Call this method from a MasterVO's createViewLinkAccessorVO to set the ViewLink properties on the attachments VO when its created as an AccessorVO. In some scenarios the AttachmentsVO will be created as an accessor (internal) view object, most likely when rendered in columnLink mode. When this happens the ViewLink definition is not associated with the AttachmentsVO and filtering for cateory and custom data security will not work. To resolve this issue call this method from the Master VO (VO who view links to AttachmentsVO) createViewLinkAccessorVO overriden method as shown in the code snippet below. If the attachments implementation matches the following criteria then the following method must be put into the Master VO:
  • Attachments component is used in column link mode.
  • The view link contains the OAF_ATTACHMENT_CATEGORY property for category filtering - OR - custom data security is applied
The calling of setAccessorValues when the above criteria is not met will not case any side effects. 

  protected ViewObjectImpl createViewLinkAccessorVO(AssociationDefImpl assocDef,
                                                     String voName,
                                                     ViewDefImpl vDef,
                                                     ViewLinkDefImpl vlDef)
  {
    ViewObjectImpl vo = super.createViewLinkAccessorVO(assocDef, voName, vDef, vlDef);
    if(vo instanceof AttachmentsVOImpl)
    {
      ((AttachmentsVOImpl) vo).setAccessorValues(this, vlDef);
    }
    return vo;
  }

Parameters:
masterVO - the view object who has a view link to Attachments VO.
vlDef - the MasterVO to AttachmentsVO view link definition.

prepareVOForQuery

public void prepareVOForQuery()

Restrict the query to apply design time and data security filters.

The design time portion restricts the query to only retrieve attachments whose category matches those in the comma separated list of custom categories against the associated viewlink, if any, prior to executing the query. If there is no viewlink or custom category value then no restriction is applied.

The data security portion restricts the query to only retrieve attachments whose categories the user has been granted access to.


Overrides:
prepareVOForQuery in class OAViewObjectImpl

populateRedlineAttributes

public void populateRedlineAttributes(java.lang.String sourceEntityName,
                                      java.lang.String sourcePk1Value,
                                      java.lang.String sourcePk2Value,
                                      java.lang.String sourcePk3Value,
                                      java.lang.String sourcePk4Value,
                                      java.lang.String sourcePk5Value)

Internal ApplCore use only

Populate the redline attributes of the current set of attachments based on the attachments for the master key passed in.

This was added for redlining support.

This is to be used where there is a View Link between the master VO and the attachmetns VO. The view link will be interrogated to find the master VO (parent) row and retrieve its entity name and pk1-5values.

Parameters:
sourceEntityName - Business object name for the source of the redline attachments.
sourcePk1Value - First primary key value for the source of the redline attachments.
sourcePk2Value - Second primary key value for the source of the redline attachments.
sourcePk3Value - Third primary key value for the source of the redline attachments.
sourcePk4Value - Fourth primary key value for the source of the redline attachments.
sourcePk5Value - Fifth primary key value for the source of the redline attachments.
See Also:
